# Testing (Target: 100%) — MANDATORY

Testing is **required**, not optional. A solution without tests is incomplete.

- Unit-test all critical pure logic (validators, utils, prompt builders, parsers).
- Integration-test API routes: valid request, invalid request, missing env key.
- Component-test key UI states (form validation, loading, error, results) when feasible.
- Cover happy path, edge cases, and error paths.
- Tests must pass via `npm test`.
- Use Vitest + React Testing Library.
- Mock external services (OpenAI, DB) in tests — never call live APIs.

**When adding or changing logic, always add or update tests in the same change.**

**Checklist:**
- [ ] Zod schemas tested with valid and invalid inputs.
- [ ] Core utility functions have unit tests.
- [ ] API route returns 422 on bad input, 500 on mocked service failure.
- [ ] At least one component test (loading, error, or results render).
- [ ] `npm test` script exists in `package.json` and all tests pass.
